## Hard Rules

### Dependencies
- ❌ Never install a new dependency without asking first
- ❌ Never upgrade major versions without explicit approval
- ✅ Prefer built-in solutions over external packages

### Database
- ❌ Never modify the database schema without showing the migration plan
- ✅ All migrations must be reversible
- ✅ Use [your ORM/query builder] for all database access

### API Patterns
- ✅ All API calls go through [your API layer, e.g., Convex functions]
- ❌ Never make direct database calls from frontend components
- ✅ All endpoints must have proper error handling

### Environment & Secrets
- ✅ Environment variables go in `.env.local`, never hardcoded
- ❌ Never commit secrets (I will find you and I will revert you)
- ✅ Use [your secret management, e.g., Vercel env vars, Doppler]

### Code Organization
- ✅ Max [150] lines per component file
- ✅ One component per file
- ✅ [Your folder structure rules, e.g., /app for pages, /components for UI]

---

## Patterns

### Component Architecture
- ✅ Use server components by default (if Next.js)
- ✅ Client components only when interactivity is required
- ✅ [Your component composition rules]

### Error Handling
- ✅ Error boundaries on every route segment
- ✅ All user-facing errors must have user-friendly messages
- ✅ Log errors to [your error tracking, e.g., Sentry, LogRocket]

### Validation
- ✅ [Your validation library, e.g., Zod] validation on every user input
- ✅ Validate on both client and server
- ✅ Return typed errors

### State Management
- ✅ [Your state patterns, e.g., Server state in React Query, UI state in useState]
- ✅ No prop drilling beyond 2 levels
- ✅ Use context for truly global state only

### TypeScript
- ✅ Strict mode enabled
- ✅ No `any` types (use `unknown` if needed)
- ✅ All function parameters must be typed
- ✅ All API responses must be typed

---

## Failure Conditions (Global)

### Styling
- ❌ No inline styles (use [your styling system])
- ❌ No magic numbers (use design tokens/constants)
- ❌ No pixel-perfect positioning (design for responsive)

### Code Quality
- ❌ No console.logs in production code
- ❌ No commented-out code blocks
- ❌ No TODO comments without GitHub issues linked
- ❌ No single-letter variable names (except loop indices)

### Security
- ❌ No unescaped user input in HTML
- ❌ No eval() or Function() constructor
- ❌ No client-side secrets
- ❌ No unvalidated redirects

### Performance
- ❌ No unoptimized images (use next/image or your optimizer)
- ❌ No blocking operations in render
- ❌ No fetching in loops

